{
  "name": "Missed Call → Instant Text Back",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Missed Call → Instant Text Back\n\n**What it does:**\nWhen a call is missed on your GHL phone number, GHL fires a webhook to this workflow. It checks if the call was during business hours (8am–8pm EST), sends the appropriate SMS via GHL API, moves the contact to \"Attempted Contact\" pipeline stage, waits 30 minutes, then sends you an internal follow-up reminder email.\n\n**Credentials to configure:**\n1. **GHL API Key** — Settings → Business Profile → API Key\n2. **SMTP Email** — For internal notification emails\n\n**Setup steps:**\n1. Import this workflow and activate it to get the webhook URL\n2. In GHL → Settings → Phone Numbers → your number → Missed Call Webhook: paste the webhook URL\n3. Replace `{{GHL_API_KEY}}` in all HTTP Request nodes\n4. Replace `{{GHL_PIPELINE_ID}}` and `{{GHL_ATTEMPTED_CONTACT_STAGE_ID}}` with actual IDs\n5. Configure SMTP credentials in n8n\n6. Test by calling your GHL number and not answering\n\n**Business hours logic:**\n- Uses America/New_York timezone (EST/EDT)\n- Business hours: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM\n- After hours: 8:00 PM – 8:00 AM\n- Different SMS templates for each",
        "height": 480,
        "width": 420,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "notes-node",
      "name": "Setup Instructions",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [40, 40]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "missed-call",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "webhook-trigger",
      "name": "GHL Missed Call Webhook",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [520, 300],
      "webhookId": "missed-call"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={\"status\":\"received\"}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "respond-webhook",
      "name": "Respond OK",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [740, 160]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "assignments": {
          "assignments": [
            {
              "id": "field-contact-id",
              "name": "contactId",
              "value": "={{ $json.body.contactId }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "field-contact-phone",
              "name": "contactPhone",
              "value": "={{ $json.body.contactPhone || $json.body.phone }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "field-contact-name",
              "name": "contactName",
              "value": "={{ $json.body.contactName || $json.body.firstName || 'there' }}",
              "type": "string"
            },
            {
              "id": "field-missed-time",
              "name": "missedCallTime",
              "value": "={{ $json.body.missedCallTime || new Date().toISOString() }}",
              "type": "string"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "set-call-data",
      "name": "Set Call Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [740, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Check if missed call was during business hours (8am-8pm EST)\nconst callTime = $input.first().json.missedCallTime;\nconst callDate = new Date(callTime);\n\n// Convert to EST/EDT\nconst estOptions = { timeZone: 'America/New_York', hour: 'numeric', hour12: false };\nconst estHour = parseInt(new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', estOptions).format(callDate));\n\nconst isBusinessHours = estHour >= 8 && estHour < 20; // 8am to 8pm\n\nconst formattedTime = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {\n  timeZone: 'America/New_York',\n  hour: 'numeric',\n  minute: '2-digit',\n  hour12: true\n}).format(callDate);\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...($input.first().json),\n    isBusinessHours,\n    estHour,\n    formattedTime\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "check-business-hours",
      "name": "Check Business Hours",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [960, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": true,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "strict"
          },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "condition-biz-hours",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.isBusinessHours }}",
              "rightValue": true,
              "operator": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "operation": "equals"
              }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "is-business-hours",
      "name": "Business Hours?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [1180, 340]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "=https://rest.gohighlevel.com/v1/contacts/{{ $('Set Call Data').item.json.contactId }}/messages/",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "Authorization",
              "value": "Bearer {{GHL_API_KEY}}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Content-Type",
              "value": "application/json"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"type\": \"SMS\",\n  \"message\": \"Hey {{ $('Set Call Data').item.json.contactName }}! Sorry I missed your call — I'm with a client right now. I'll call you back within 30 minutes. Or grab a time here: calendly.com/localvex – Levi, LocalVex\"\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
